The paper focuses on the link prediction problem for knowledge graphs using neural embeddings, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the embeddings, which involves analyzing and comparing data, making it relevant to databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for scalable link prediction, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
